name: Coleoptera by Bryan Kring
description:
Artist: Bryan Kring
Size: 3.25” x 3.75” x1.75”
Edition: 98 

This box contains an unidentified specimen of the Coleoptera order. Clues to the meaning of this mysterious insect can be found on the cover label and map which document its origin. When the knob at the base of the box is pulled the beetle's wings spread open to reveal a hidden passenger.

This piece is made from paper. The various "body parts" of the beetle were printed on a letterpress and then individually hand painted with watercolor and oil sticks. The pieces were then cut out and assembled with meticulous care. The handmade box is wrapped with brown paper and includes an glass window which encloses the insect.

name: The Fall, Limited Edition Diorama Storybook
description:
Artist: Bryan Kring.

The little astronaut in this diorama hangs suspended among the clouds over the city below. Frozen in his terminal fall he is left to contemplate the point to life for all eternity, or until the glue on his back breaks. 

This book is small enough to fit in your hand. It is designed to be displayed open on a shelf or hung securely from the attached tie string. 

The printing is a blend of etching and letterpress. The outer "skin" of the box was printed from hand wiped plates on an etching press. The text and drawings within the box were printed on a letterpress. Every piece was carefully printed, cut, and assembled by hand.

Size: 3.25" x3.25" x 1"

Edition: 100

name: President James Madison
description:
Title: James Madison (2008)
Dimensions: 12” x 12”
Media: Acrylic on Canvas

James Madison, a Democratic-Republican, was known as “Father of the Constitution.” During his presidency, Louisiana (1812), and Indiana (1816) became part of the United States. He was a layer and an Episcopalian. Madison had no children and was only about 5′4″ and under 100 lbs. His nose became frostbitten while campaigning in 1788, leaving a permanent scar.

name: President James Garfield
description:
Title: James Abram Garfield (2008)
Dimensions: 12” x 12”
Media: Acrylic on Canvas

James A. Garfield was the 20th President of the United States. His religion was known as Disciples of Christ and he was a public official, Republican, and teacher. Garfield was able simultaneously write Latin with one hand and Greek with the other. He was 6ft tall and 185 lbs when he was elected. He was shot by Leon F. Guiteau on July 2, 1881 and was fed rectally after he was shot. He died 80 days later and served as President only 6 months.

name: President Benjamin Harrison
description:
Artist: Lena Verderano Reynoso
Title: Benjamin Harrison (2008)
Dimensions: 12” x 12”
Media: Acrylic on Canvas

Benjamin Harrison was the 23rd President of the United States. He was 5ft. 6inches tall and was a Presbyterian, Lawyer, and Republican. Harrison’s handshake was said to be “like a wilted petunia” (See TR and Will: A Friendship that Split the Republican Party, 1969). When he was a General, he developed a skin rash that caused him to wear gloves all of the time.
